<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In the first paragraph of the documentation:
bq. The first parameter $name can be a simple string, in which case the correlation name is generated automatically. If you want to specify the correlation name, the first parameter must be an associative array in which the key is the physical table name, and the value is the correlation name. For example, array('table' =&gt; 'alias'). The correlation name is prepended to all columns fetched for this table.</p>

<p>is the sentence "For example, array('table' =&gt; 'alias')."</p>

<p>The order of the array is wrong. It should be array('alias' =&gt; 'table')</p>

